TITLE: Reset Keys with `values()` in PHP
DESCRIPTION: The `values()` method returns a new collection with the keys reset to consecutive integers, starting from 0. This is useful for re-indexing a collection after filtering or manipulation. Requires a Laravel Collection instance with potentially non-sequential or non-integer keys.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/collections.md#_snippet_140

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
$collection = collect([
    10 => ['product' => 'Desk', 'price' => 200],
    11 => ['product' => 'Desk', 'price' => 200],
]);

$values = $collection->values();

$values->all();

/*
    [
        0 => ['product' => 'Desk', 'price' => 200],
        1 => ['product' => 'Desk', 'price' => 200],
    ]
*/
```

