TITLE: Defining an Accessor in Laravel Eloquent
DESCRIPTION: Example of defining an accessor method for the first_name attribute that capitalizes the first letter of the name when accessed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/eloquent-mutators.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Casts\Attribute;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;

class User extends Model
{
    /**
     * Get the user's first name.
     */
    protected function firstName(): Attribute
    {
        return Attribute::make(
            get: fn (string $value) => ucfirst($value),
        );
    }
}
```

