TITLE: Using Queue Looping Method for Database Transaction Rollback in Laravel
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use the 'looping' method on the Queue facade to specify a callback that executes before the worker attempts to fetch a job from the queue. In this example, it's used to rollback any open database transactions left by previously failed jobs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/queues.md#2025-04-21_snippet_117

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\DB;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Queue;

Queue::looping(function () {
    while (DB::transactionLevel() > 0) {
        DB::rollBack();
    }
});
```

