TITLE: Converting Authorization Codes to Access Tokens in Laravel
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to convert an authorization code to an access token using Laravel's HTTP client. It includes state validation and a POST request to the OAuth token endpoint.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/passport.md#2025-04-21_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Http;

Route::get('/callback', function (Request $request) {
    $state = $request->session()->pull('state');

    throw_unless(
        strlen($state) > 0 && $state === $request->state,
        InvalidArgumentException::class,
        'Invalid state value.'
    );

    $response = Http::asForm()->post('http://passport-app.test/oauth/token', [
        'grant_type' => 'authorization_code',
        'client_id' => 'client-id',
        'client_secret' => 'client-secret',
        'redirect_uri' => 'http://third-party-app.com/callback',
        'code' => $request->code,
    ]);

    return $response->json();
});
```

