TITLE: Implementing a Paginate Query Object in Laravel
DESCRIPTION: Creates a Paginate query object class that handles pagination logic for Laravel queries. This class accepts sorting and pagination parameters and returns a LengthAwarePaginator instance when invoked with a query builder.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/queries.md#2025-04-21_snippet_42

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Scopes;

use Illuminate\Contracts\Pagination\LengthAwarePaginator;
use Illuminate\Database\Query\Builder;

class Paginate
{
    public function __construct(
        private string $sortBy = 'timestamp',
        private string $sortDirection = 'desc',
        private string $perPage = 25,
    ) {
        //
    }

    public function __invoke(Builder $query): LengthAwarePaginator
    {
        return $query->orderBy($this->sortBy, $this->sortDirection)
            ->paginate($this->perPage, pageName: 'p');
    }
}
```

