TITLE: Flattening Collections with collapseWithKeys() in PHP
DESCRIPTION: The `collapseWithKeys` method flattens a collection of arrays or collections into a single collection, preserving the keys from the original nested structures. This is useful when the keys of the nested items are significant.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/collections.md#_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$collection = collect([
    ['first'  => collect([1, 2, 3])],
    ['second' => [4, 5, 6]],
    ['third'  => collect([7, 8, 9])]
]);

$collapsed = $collection->collapseWithKeys();

$collapsed->all();

// [
//     'first'  => [1, 2, 3],
//     'second' => [4, 5, 6],
//     'third'  => [7, 8, 9],
// ]
```

