TITLE: Mapping Laravel Collection Items to Groups (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Iterates over the collection, applying a callback that should return a single key/value pair. This method is used to group items based on the key returned by the callback, creating a new collection where keys represent groups and values are collections of items belonging to that group.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/collections.md#_snippet_73

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$collection = collect([
    [
        'name' => 'John Doe',
        'department' => 'Sales',
    ],
    [
        'name' => 'Jane Doe',
        'department' => 'Sales',
    ],
    [
        'name' => 'Johnny Doe',
        'department' => 'Marketing',
    ]
]);

$grouped = $collection->mapToGroups(function (array $item, int $key) {
    return [$item['department'] => $item['name']];
});

$grouped->all();

/*
    [
        'Sales' => ['John Doe', 'Jane Doe'],
        'Marketing' => ['Johnny Doe'],
    ]
*/

$grouped->get('Sales')->all();

// ['John Doe', 'Jane Doe']
```

