TITLE: Using Laravel Pipeline Facade to Process Inputs Through Multiple Callables in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use Laravel's Pipeline facade to send an input instance (e.g. a User object) through a series of closures or invokable classes. Each callable receives the input and a $next closure to invoke the next stage, enabling modifications or side effects on the input. After all stages, a final callback passed to then() is called with the processed input. This pattern is similar to middleware chaining and requires Illuminate\Support\Facades\Pipeline. The example uses closures to manipulate user input with the ability to short-circuit or alter data.
