TITLE: Encrypting Values in a Laravel Controller
DESCRIPTION: Example of encrypting a user's API token in a Laravel controller. The token is encrypted using the Crypt facade before being stored in the database, providing secure storage of sensitive data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/encryption.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use Illuminate\Http\RedirectResponse;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Crypt;

class DigitalOceanTokenController extends Controller
{
    /**
     * Store a DigitalOcean API token for the user.
     */
    public function store(Request $request): RedirectResponse
    {
        $request->user()->fill([
            'token' => Crypt::encryptString($request->token),
        ])->save();

        return redirect('/secrets');
    }
}
```

