TITLE: Configuring Maximum Exceptions for Laravel Queue Jobs
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of a Laravel job class with maxExceptions property that limits the number of unhandled exceptions before the job fails, separate from the regular retry count.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/queues.md#2025-04-21_snippet_40

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Jobs;

use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Redis;

class ProcessPodcast implements ShouldQueue
{
    /**
     * The number of times the job may be attempted.
     *
     * @var int
     */
    public $tries = 25;

    /**
     * The maximum number of unhandled exceptions to allow before failing.
     *
     * @var int
     */
    public $maxExceptions = 3;

    /**
     * Execute the job.
     */
    public function handle(): void
    {
        Redis::throttle('key')->allow(10)->every(60)->then(function () {
            // Lock obtained, process the podcast...
        }, function () {
            // Unable to obtain lock...
            return $this->release(10);
        });
    }
}
```

