TITLE: Getting Previous Item with before() in PHP
DESCRIPTION: The `before` method retrieves the item immediately preceding a specified item or the first item matching a callback. It returns `null` if the target item is not found or is the first item in the collection. Strict comparison can be enabled.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/collections.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$collection = collect([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]);

$collection->before(3);

// 2

$collection->before(1);

// null

collect([2, 4, 6, 8])->before('4', strict: true);

// null

collect([2, 4, 6, 8])->before(function (int $item, int $key) {
    return $item > 5;
});

// 4
```

