TITLE: Using throttle() Method with Laravel LazyCollection in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Shows the throttle() method of Laravel's LazyCollection which delays enumeration of each item by a specified number of seconds, enabling rate-limiting scenarios such as calling external APIs at a controlled pace. Requires Laravel's LazyCollection and model querying capabilities. The example throttles User model queries where VIP users are processed one per second, ideal for managing API request limits or resource usage.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/collections.md#_snippet_161

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use App\Models\User;

User::where('vip', true)
    ->cursor()
    ->throttle(seconds: 1)
    ->each(function (User $user) {
        // Call external API...
    });
```

