TITLE: Mapping Array Values with `Arr::map()` - PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use `Arr::map()` to iterate through an array and apply a callback function to each value. The original array values are replaced by the values returned by the callback function, effectively transforming the array.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/helpers.md#_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Illuminate\Support\Arr;

$array = ['first' => 'james', 'last' => 'kirk'];

$mapped = Arr::map($array, function (string $value, string $key) {
    return ucfirst($value);
});

// ['first' => 'James', 'last' => 'Kirk']
```

