TITLE: Conditional Chunking with chunkWhile() in PHP
DESCRIPTION: The `chunkWhile` method breaks a collection into smaller collections based on the result of a given callback function. A new chunk is started when the callback returns `false`. The callback receives the current value, key, and the chunk being built so far.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/collections.md#_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$collection = collect(str_split('AABBCCCD'));

$chunks = $collection->chunkWhile(function (string $value, int $key, Collection $chunk) {
    return $value === $chunk->last();
});

$chunks->all();

// [['A', 'A'], ['B', 'B'], ['C', 'C', 'C'], ['D']]
```

