TITLE: Scoped Event Faking in Laravel Tests (PHPUnit)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use scoped event faking in Laravel tests using PHPUnit. It shows how to fake events for a specific portion of the test while allowing normal event dispatching outside that scope.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/events.md#2025-04-21_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace Tests\Feature;

use App\Events\OrderCreated;
use App\Models\Order;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Event;
use Tests\TestCase;

class ExampleTest extends TestCase
{
    /**
     * Test order process.
     */
    public function test_orders_can_be_processed(): void
    {
        $order = Event::fakeFor(function () {
            $order = Order::factory()->create();

            Event::assertDispatched(OrderCreated::class);

            return $order;
        });

        // Events are dispatched as normal and observers will run ...
        $order->update([...]);
    }
}
```

