TITLE: Handling Side-Effects in Middleware for Precognitive Requests in Laravel
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to check if a request is precognitive before executing side-effects in middleware. It uses the `isPrecognitive` method to conditionally increment an interaction count.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/precognition.md#2025-04-21_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Http\Middleware;

use App\Facades\Interaction;
use Closure;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class InteractionMiddleware
{
    /**
     * Handle an incoming request.
     */
    public function handle(Request $request, Closure $next): mixed
    {
        if (! $request->isPrecognitive()) {
            Interaction::incrementFor($request->user());
        }

        return $next($request);
    }
}
