TITLE: Defining Custom Keyboard Macros in Laravel Dusk
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define custom keyboard macros using the Keyboard::macro() method in a service provider.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/dusk.md#2025-04-21_snippet_27

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Providers;

use Facebook\WebDriver\WebDriverKeys;
use Illuminate\Support\ServiceProvider;
use Laravel\Dusk\Keyboard;
use Laravel\Dusk\OperatingSystem;

class DuskServiceProvider extends ServiceProvider
{
    /**
     * Register Dusk's browser macros.
     */
    public function boot(): void
    {
        Keyboard::macro('copy', function (string $element = null) {
            $this->type([
                OperatingSystem::onMac() ? WebDriverKeys::META : WebDriverKeys::CONTROL, 'c',
            ]);

            return $this;
        });

        Keyboard::macro('paste', function (string $element = null) {
            $this->type([
                OperatingSystem::onMac() ? WebDriverKeys::META : WebDriverKeys::CONTROL, 'v',
            ]);

            return $this;
        });
    }
}
```

