TITLE: Handling Unexpected Null Scope in Laravel Pennant
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to register a listener for the UnexpectedNullScopeEncountered event in Laravel Pennant. It demonstrates how to override the default graceful behavior by aborting the request with a 500 error.
SOURCE: https://github.com/laravel/docs/blob/12.x/pennant.md#2025-04-21_snippet_35

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Log;
use Laravel\Pennant\Events\UnexpectedNullScopeEncountered;

/**
 * Bootstrap any application services.
 */
public function boot(): void
{
    Event::listen(UnexpectedNullScopeEncountered::class, fn () => abort(500));
}
```

